00:20:05,580 --> 00:20:08,220
No, I'm already busy
looking after my kids.

277
00:20:08,280 --> 00:20:09,290
Right.

278
00:20:09,390 --> 00:20:12,220
Ae-rin, are you getting married
anytime soon?

279
00:20:12,290 --> 00:20:14,560
No, I don't plan on getting married.

280
00:20:14,620 --> 00:20:16,430
What? You want to stay single forever?

281
00:20:16,490 --> 00:20:19,360
If you're just using that as an excuse
because it's too late and embarrassing,

282
00:20:19,430 --> 00:20:21,100
don't be.

283
00:20:21,160 --> 00:20:24,000
No need to be embarrassed
in front of your old friends!

284
00:20:24,270 --> 00:20:25,570
It's fine.

285
00:20:26,140 --> 00:20:28,100
Is Da-jung coming?

286
00:20:28,200 --> 00:20:30,310
You think she would? She got divorced.

287
00:20:32,880 --> 00:20:33,880
Why?

288
00:20:34,410 --> 00:20:37,110
Is there a rule that you can't come
to a reunion if you're divorced?

289
00:20:37,180 --> 00:20:39,450
It's embarrassing!

290
00:20:39,780 --> 00:20:41,480
- What?
- To be honest,

291
00:20:41,550 --> 00:20:44,650
I was embarrassed for her
every time she came.

292
00:20:44,890 --> 00:20:48,090
Everyone here knows that she got
knocked up as a teen.

293
00:20:48,790 --> 00:20:51,700
Not only that, she never got to
go to college in time,

294
00:20:51,760 --> 00:20:54,160
married an incapable husband,
and got divorced.

295
00:20:54,860 --> 00:20:58,470
Da-jung is really the epitome
of all things unfortunate.

296
00:20:59,870 --> 00:21:00,870
Hey!

297
00:21:01,810 --> 00:21:04,610
Who are you to evaluate
other people's lives?

298
00:21:05,110 --> 00:21:06,480
Did Da-jung say that she felt unhappy?

299
00:21:07,010 --> 00:21:09,110
Did she say that herself?

300
00:21:09,280 --> 00:21:10,580
Do we really need to hear her say that
to know?

301
00:21:10,650 --> 00:21:11,680
Of course!

302
00:21:11,920 --> 00:21:15,450
You said that you wouldn't have married
your husband had it not been

303
00:21:15,520 --> 00:21:17,890
for his money, and that his face looks
like a dumpster.

304
00:21:18,050 --> 00:21:22,130
Fact is what comes out
of the person themselves!

305
00:21:22,560 --> 00:21:25,830
Chu Ae-rin! We can't even worry
for our old friend?

306
00:21:25,900 --> 00:21:28,430
Oh, old friend?

307
00:21:39,010 --> 00:21:40,440
(Divorce Lawyer Chu Ae-rin)
I got a new name card.

308
00:21:40,880 --> 00:21:42,950
Give me a call when you need me.

309
00:21:43,110 --> 00:21:45,050
I'll give you an old friend discount

310
00:21:45,950 --> 00:21:48,320
because I worry for you all.

311
00:21:50,590 --> 00:21:52,760
(Serim High School Alumni Reunion)

312
00:21:53,060 --> 00:21:54,820
- Hey.
- What...

313
00:21:54,890 --> 00:21:56,490
What's wrong with her?

314
00:21:56,990 --> 00:21:58,390
Why is she causing a scene?

315
00:22:02,630 --> 00:22:04,270
I'm never coming to a reunion again!

316
00:22:07,940 --> 00:22:09,310
I wonder how she's doing.

317
00:22:20,350 --> 00:22:21,320
Da-jung!

318
00:22:21,920 --> 00:22:23,250
Are you free?

319
00:22:24,990 --> 00:22:26,390
Let's get a beer.

320
00:22:30,430 --> 00:22:31,530
How refreshing.

321
00:22:33,260 --> 00:22:36,400
It's nice to drink in broad daylight.
It's been a while.

322
00:22:37,330 --> 00:22:38,900
One more, please!

323
00:22:40,000 --> 00:22:42,940
Did something happen
at the school reunion?

324
00:22:44,140 --> 00:22:46,680
What? No, nothing happened.

325
00:22:47,010 --> 00:22:49,050
I left because it was no fun.

326
00:22:49,350 --> 00:22:52,480
Hanging out with you
is the most fun for me.

327
00:22:52,550 --> 00:22:54,150
Same here.

328
00:22:55,050 --> 00:22:58,250
Then, why don't we go on a trip
next weekend?

329
00:22:58,620 --> 00:23:00,690
We can go somewhere close

330
00:23:00,760 --> 00:23:02,330
and have a cup of coffee.

331
00:23:02,590 --> 00:23:04,160
And let's take a lot of photos too.

332
00:23:04,590 --> 00:23:07,730
What a surprise.
You're the busiest woman I know.

333
00:23:08,870 --> 00:23:10,700
I wasn't the busy one between us.

334
00:23:10,770 --> 00:23:12,270
You always said no to my offer.

335
00:23:13,800 --> 00:23:14,800
Right.

336
00:23:15,540 --> 00:23:17,410
I did say no.

337
00:23:19,140 --> 00:23:20,780
I was just kidding.

338
00:23:20,840 --> 00:23:22,910
If you feel bad about it, I feel bad too.

339
00:23:24,280 --> 00:23:26,480
It's nothing. I'm just envious.

340
00:23:27,080 --> 00:23:28,050
Of what?

341
00:23:28,850 --> 00:23:30,950
You're free and passionate.

342
00:23:31,020 --> 00:23:34,120
You're enjoying your life.
I'm so envious of that.

343
00:23:34,660 --> 00:23:35,660
Really?

344
00:23:36,230 --> 00:23:38,760
I'm going paragliding again this time.

345
00:23:38,830 --> 00:23:39,930
Want to join me?

346
00:23:40,430 --> 00:23:41,500
Really?

347
00:23:42,100 --> 00:23:43,970
Whenever you went paragliding,

348
00:23:44,030 --> 00:23:45,900
I always wanted to go with you.

349
00:23:46,070 --> 00:23:47,070
Join me.

350
00:23:49,140 --> 00:23:50,440
It's my kids.

351
00:23:51,670 --> 00:23:54,380
I can't do anything
that's physically dangerous.

352
00:23:55,880 --> 00:23:58,280
What if I get into an accident?
What about my kids?

353
00:23:59,180 --> 00:24:00,980
They are still in high school.

354
00:24:02,050 --> 00:24:04,750
Gosh. You are indeed a mother.

355
00:24:05,090 --> 00:24:07,620
Forget it. Let's just drink today.

356
00:24:08,160 --> 00:24:09,160
Let's do that.

357
00:24:22,810 --> 00:24:24,770
(Seo Ji-ho)

358
00:24:28,040 --> 00:24:29,150
Whatever.

359
00:24:29,210 --> 00:24:31,010
That's her. Hong Si-a.

360
00:24:31,880 --> 00:24:35,490
What? Gu Ja-sung asked
someone like her to go out with him?

361
00:24:35,550 --> 00:24:36,620
Whatever.

362
00:24:36,690 --> 00:24:38,450
But she dumped him
when she looks like that.

363
00:24:38,520 --> 00:24:40,760
My gosh. She must be
very confident of herself.

364
00:24:40,820 --> 00:24:42,430
She must think she's pretty.

365
00:24:42,490 --> 00:24:44,590
Exactly. She's ridiculous.

366
00:24:44,660 --> 00:24:47,300
- Let's just ignore them.
- Right. Did you know?

367
00:24:47,360 --> 00:24:48,560
Jung Da-jung.

368
00:24:49,030 --> 00:24:50,230
That's her mom.

369
00:24:50,530 --> 00:24:52,570
I see. That woman who got splashed?

370
00:24:53,140 --> 00:24:56,370
I knew it.
She's trashy just like her mother.

371
00:24:56,870 --> 00:24:58,610
Hey, by the way, she must think

372
00:24:58,680 --> 00:25:00,610
having kids at an early age is
something to brag about.

373
00:25:00,680 --> 00:25:02,180
How can she be on TV?

374
00:25:02,610 --> 00:25:03,880
How humiliating.

375
00:25:04,280 --> 00:25:05,820
Hey, she might hear you.

376
00:25:06,350 --> 00:25:07,350
Seriously.

377
00:25:09,990 --> 00:25:13,120
- What are you doing?
- I can put up with criticisms about me,

378
00:25:13,190 --> 00:25:15,020
but not when they are about my mom.

379
00:25:15,120 --> 00:25:16,260
Let go of me.

380
00:25:16,330 --> 00:25:18,530
- Apologize.
- You must be out of your mind.

381
00:25:20,030 --> 00:25:22,600
- I'm sorry.
- Sorry about what?

382
00:25:23,830 --> 00:25:27,500
I badmouthed your mother.
I'm sorry about that.

383
00:25:32,210 --> 00:25:33,910
Hey, are you okay?

384
00:25:38,150 --> 00:25:39,250
Who are you?

385
00:25:40,650 --> 00:25:41,680
Hong Si-a?

386
00:25:42,520 --> 00:25:44,050
You must be out of your mind.

387
00:25:48,420 --> 00:25:50,860
You can't go like this.
Where do you think you're going?

388
00:25:51,590 --> 00:25:53,600
If you want to leave, kneel and apologize.

389
00:25:53,660 --> 00:25:55,730
Then, maybe, I'll consider letting you go.

390
00:25:59,590 --> 00:26:01,430
- Let go of me.
- No.

391
00:26:03,860 --> 00:26:05,430
Are you crazy?

392
00:26:05,500 --> 00:26:07,430
- Gosh.
- Hey.

393
00:26:07,500 --> 00:26:08,940
- Are you okay?
- Hey.

394
00:26:11,470 --> 00:26:14,110
Hey, get them. Get them now!

395
00:26:14,810 --> 00:26:15,840
Hey!

396
00:26:16,310 --> 00:26:17,380
Darn it.

397
00:26:17,980 --> 00:26:19,010
Hey!

398
00:26:21,520 --> 00:26:22,980
Stop right there!

399
00:26:23,620 --> 00:26:24,620
Hey!

400
00:26:25,690 --> 00:26:27,390
Hey!

401
00:26:29,420 --> 00:26:31,060
You're really not going to the PC cafe?

402
00:26:31,790 --> 00:26:33,690
- Let's go.
- I said no.

403
00:26:33,760 --> 00:26:35,330
Let's just go.

404
00:26:46,340 --> 00:26:47,370
Hey, stop them.

405
00:26:53,250 --> 00:26:54,310
What's going on?

406
00:26:57,650 --> 00:27:00,650
It's none of your business.
Get out of my way.

407
00:27:00,820 --> 00:27:02,120
It is my business.

408
00:27:06,190 --> 00:27:07,590
Don't bother Hong Si-a.

409
00:27:09,100 --> 00:27:11,130
If you do, I won't let that slide.

410
00:27:15,870 --> 00:27:16,940
Oh, right.

411
00:27:18,270 --> 00:27:19,970
Don't bother that guy either.

412
00:27:23,680 --> 00:27:25,150
Darn it.

413
00:27:26,610 --> 00:27:27,610
Let's go.

414
00:27:31,950 --> 00:27:33,090
What?

415
00:27:54,440 --> 00:27:57,110
Are you okay? Are you hurt?

416
00:27:59,950 --> 00:28:01,110
I'm okay.

417
00:28:01,380 --> 00:28:02,520
Do I make you

418
00:28:03,020 --> 00:28:04,180
uncomfortable?

419
00:28:08,460 --> 00:28:09,520
No.

420
00:28:09,920 --> 00:28:11,690
You're an awful liar,

421
00:28:12,790 --> 00:28:13,860
Si-a.

422
00:28:18,900 --> 00:28:19,970
I'm sorry.

423
00:28:20,030 --> 00:28:21,500
Why are you sorry?

424
00:28:21,670 --> 00:28:23,470
I'm the one who made things uncomfortable

425
00:28:24,740 --> 00:28:25,740
between us.

426
00:28:27,040 --> 00:28:28,680
But you can forget about what I said.

427
00:28:30,540 --> 00:28:32,780
I don't want to lose our friendship

428
00:28:34,880 --> 00:28:36,120
because of what I said.

429
00:28:41,890 --> 00:28:42,960
Let's go.

430
00:28:47,260 --> 00:28:48,460
Hey, Ji-ho.

431
00:28:52,370 --> 00:28:53,430
Wait up.

432
00:29:02,880 --> 00:29:03,980
Don't just stand there.

433
00:29:04,780 --> 00:29:06,010
Let's go.

434
00:29:08,780 --> 00:29:09,780
Okay.

435
00:29:21,960 --> 00:29:24,970
My gosh. I'm drunk today.

436
00:29:25,630 --> 00:29:28,600
I called a taxi. Take it when it comes.

437
00:29:31,810 --> 00:29:32,870
By the way,

438
00:29:33,640 --> 00:29:37,010
were you able to make things clear
with Woo-young?

439
00:29:37,880 --> 00:29:39,110
Don't even start.

440
00:29:39,910 --> 00:29:42,480
I thought I made things very clear,

441
00:29:43,480 --> 00:29:45,250
but he crossed the line.

442
00:29:46,550 --> 00:29:47,650
How?

443
00:29:48,860 --> 00:29:50,620
He told me that he's Hong Dae-young.

444
00:29:51,490 --> 00:29:52,530
What?

445
00:29:54,630 --> 00:29:58,600
So what do you think about that?

446
00:29:58,670 --> 00:30:00,670
What do I think?

447
00:30:00,930 --> 00:30:03,540
I just feel bad for Deok-jin.

448
00:30:11,240 --> 00:30:12,250
Da-jung.

449
00:30:13,680 --> 00:30:17,350
You told me that your heart fluttered
because he resembled Dae-young.

450
00:30:18,180 --> 00:30:20,390
Putting aside his looks,

451
00:30:20,450 --> 00:30:22,890
he has Dae-young's voice
and acts like Dae-young.

452
00:30:23,090 --> 00:30:24,290
Even I found that a bit off.

453
00:30:24,360 --> 00:30:26,790
That has never crossed your mind?

454
00:30:26,890 --> 00:30:27,930
Not at all.

455
00:30:27,990 --> 00:30:30,530
It's impossible for people to get young.

456
00:30:31,000 --> 00:30:32,100
Why is that?

457
00:30:32,900 --> 00:30:35,340
I mean, it turns out

458
00:30:35,400 --> 00:30:37,800
there are deities and aliens in our world.

459
00:30:37,900 --> 00:30:40,810
Dae-young could have gotten younger.

460
00:30:40,910 --> 00:30:43,710
You never know what can happen
in our world.

461
00:30:44,480 --> 00:30:45,480
Right.

462
00:30:47,150 --> 00:30:48,650
You are drunk.

463
00:30:52,920 --> 00:30:54,690
The taxi is here. Let's go.

464
00:30:54,750 --> 00:30:57,120
- Hey, I'm really not drunk.
- Hurry.

465
00:30:57,190 --> 00:30:59,530
Hey, I'm not drunk at all.

466
00:30:59,590 --> 00:31:01,490
This is a fact!

467
00:31:02,000 --> 00:31:03,000
Hey.

468
00:31:07,570 --> 00:31:09,140
Sorry for making you wait long.

469
00:31:09,300 --> 00:31:12,470
My grandma is leaving tomorrow.
I was helping her pack.

470
00:31:13,270 --> 00:31:15,310
- She's leaving tomorrow?
- Yes.

471
00:31:16,110 --> 00:31:17,680
Hey, Mom.

472
00:31:23,280 --> 00:31:25,020
Where are you going at this hour?

473
00:31:25,090 --> 00:31:27,990
To the park.
I'm going to practice with Woo-young.

474
00:31:28,860 --> 00:31:30,490
Don't you know what time it is?

475
00:31:31,520 --> 00:31:32,630
Did you call him out?

476
00:31:33,760 --> 00:31:36,230
- No, the thing is...
- From now on,

477
00:31:36,900 --> 00:31:38,600
don't call Si-woo out at a late hour.

478
00:31:39,800 --> 00:31:41,870
It's late, so practice tomorrow.

479
00:31:43,400 --> 00:31:44,440
Let's go, Si-woo.

480
00:31:48,010 --> 00:31:49,610
I'm sorry, Woo-young.

481
00:31:50,240 --> 00:31:51,850
I'll call you later.

482
00:32:07,060 --> 00:32:08,630
Why are you being like that to Woo-young?

483
00:32:11,100 --> 00:32:13,870
If you act cold to him, I'll feel bad.

484
00:32:14,870 --> 00:32:17,770
Si-woo. I'll be honest with you.

485
00:32:18,170 --> 00:32:22,640
I want you to keep
your distance from Woo-young.

486
00:32:23,080 --> 00:32:24,080
What?

487
00:32:25,410 --> 00:32:26,650
Why must I do that?

488
00:32:26,750 --> 00:32:27,810
It's because...

489
00:32:33,050 --> 00:32:36,320
Maybe it's because he lived abroad
for a long time,

490
00:32:36,420 --> 00:32:38,090
but I feel like he's too open-minded.

491
00:32:38,490 --> 00:32:40,160
What are you talking about?

492
00:32:40,230 --> 00:32:42,100
Did you have that kind of prejudice?

493
00:32:42,160 --> 00:32:44,960
Regardless, it's because I'm worried.

494
00:32:45,330 --> 00:32:46,870
You only hang out
with Woo-young these days,

495
00:32:46,930 --> 00:32:49,070
and you don't meet your other friends.

496
00:32:52,370 --> 00:32:54,270
I don't have any friends to hang out with.

497
00:32:57,280 --> 00:32:58,650
What do you mean?

498
00:33:01,180 --> 00:33:02,350
To be honest,

499
00:33:06,490 --> 00:33:08,520
I was bullied at school.

500
00:33:11,120 --> 00:33:12,130
What?

501
00:33:13,860 --> 00:33:17,260
Why are you telling me that now?

502
00:33:18,400 --> 00:33:19,770
How can I tell you that?

503
00:33:27,970 --> 00:33:30,640
But I'm okay now, so don't worry.

504
00:33:34,910 --> 00:33:37,850
I didn't have friends before,

505
00:33:38,850 --> 00:33:41,050
and I didn't have the courage
to play basketball.

506
00:33:41,890 --> 00:33:43,090
But after I met Woo-young,

507
00:33:44,120 --> 00:33:45,860
a lot has changed for me.

508
00:33:49,100 --> 00:33:50,160
Woo-young

509
00:33:51,600 --> 00:33:53,720
is a really good friend to me.

510
00:33:54,930 --> 00:33:55,930
Are things

511
00:33:56,900 --> 00:33:58,740
okay now?

512
00:33:59,170 --> 00:34:01,430
Yes, they are.

513
00:34:02,200 --> 00:34:03,380
It's all thanks to Woo-young.

514
00:34:35,140 --> 00:34:38,010
- Goodness.
- This must be so heavy.

515
00:34:38,080 --> 00:34:40,150
What? Woo-young.

516
00:34:40,480 --> 00:34:41,810
Didn't you go to school?

517
00:34:42,350 --> 00:34:45,080
I had something to do,
so I left school early.

518
00:34:45,750 --> 00:34:49,060
Is that so? What brings you here?

519
00:34:49,960 --> 00:34:51,990
I heard you were leaving today.

520
00:34:52,790 --> 00:34:54,430
I have to go to the bus terminal too.

521
00:34:54,630 --> 00:34:55,730
The bus terminal?

522
00:34:55,860 --> 00:34:56,860
Yes.

523
00:34:57,630 --> 00:34:59,100
Why do you need to go there?

524
00:35:01,770 --> 00:35:04,070
To see my mom.

525
00:35:17,620 --> 00:35:19,850
(Ticket Office)

526
00:35:20,550 --> 00:35:22,920
Here. One ticket to Gangneung, please.

527
00:35:24,060 --> 00:35:25,290
Thank you.

528
00:35:35,870 --> 00:35:37,770
He must have left.

529
00:35:48,010 --> 00:35:50,180
(Director's Office)

530
00:35:50,250 --> 00:35:51,250
Come in.

531
00:35:56,990 --> 00:36:00,360
I have the final score
for the probationary employees.

532
00:36:14,270 --> 00:36:15,270
What?

533
00:36:16,380 --> 00:36:17,380
What is this?

534
00:36:18,750 --> 00:36:19,980
Is this correct?

535
00:36:21,080 --> 00:36:22,080
Yes.

536
00:36:26,650 --> 00:36:28,090
Does this make sense?

537
00:36:51,880 --> 00:36:52,880
Newbies.

538
00:36:53,780 --> 00:36:54,850
Gather around.

539
00:37:03,760 --> 00:37:04,820
The results

540
00:37:08,160 --> 00:37:10,300
for the permanent employees just came out.

541
00:37:31,250 --> 00:37:32,250
Excuse me.

542
00:37:33,620 --> 00:37:36,320
What? You didn't leave yet?

543
00:37:36,920 --> 00:37:37,920
Not yet.

544
00:37:39,560 --> 00:37:40,930
Please eat this as you go.

545
00:37:43,660 --> 00:37:45,330
Your luggage is heavy,

546
00:37:45,400 --> 00:37:47,070
so be sure to take a taxi home.

547
00:37:49,540 --> 00:37:52,570
Right. Thank you.

548
00:37:54,070 --> 00:37:55,070
Then

549
